<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id522fd2b0-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6" identifier="/us/usc/t28/s114"><num value="114">§ 114.</num><heading> North Dakota</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">North Dakota constitutes one judicial district.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Court shall be held at Bismarck, Fargo, Grand Forks, and Minot.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id522fd2b1-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/111/174/s3">Pub. L. 111–174, § 3</ref>, <date date="2010-05-27">May 27, 2010</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/1216">124 Stat. 1216</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id522fd2b2-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id522fd2b3-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="priorProvisions" id="id522fd2b4-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Prior Provisions</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">A prior section 114, <ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646">act June 25, 1948, ch. 646</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/886">62 Stat. 886</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/95/408/s3/b">Pub. L. 95–408, § 3(b)</ref>, <date date="1978-10-02">Oct. 2, 1978</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/92/883">92 Stat. 883</ref>, which provided that North Dakota consisted of one judicial district comprising four divisions, was repealed by <ref href="/us/pl/111/174/s3">Pub. L. 111–174, § 3</ref>, <date date="2010-05-27">May 27, 2010</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/1216">124 Stat. 1216</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
